stories.title: Pakistan gain upper hand
stories.summary:
The West Indies cricket team lost for the first time in six
matches this past Wednesday when they were defeated in the first
of three Cable and Wireless one-day finals against Pakistan at
Kensington Oval in Barbados

stories.title: Disciplined bowling helps Pakistan take 1-0 lead
stories.summary:
Bridgetown (Barbados), April 20: Pakistan struck a timely blow when
they defeated the West Indies by 17 runs in the first final of the
triangular one-day series here on Wednesday (partly reported in
Thursday's edition)
